# Mermaid diagrams

When writing or editing Mermaid diagrams (in Markdown or elsewhere), follow the official syntax reference:

**https://mermaid.js.org/intro/syntax-reference.html**

- Start each diagram with a **diagram type** declaration (e.g. `flowchart LR`, `sequenceDiagram`), then the definitions.
- **Diagram breakers:** Avoid unquoted `end`; wrap it in quotation marks if needed. In `%%` comments, avoid `{}`. Nested node labels can break flowcharts — wrap in quotes if needed.
- Use the [Mermaid Live Editor](https://mermaid.live) to validate or iterate on diagrams.
